# TODO Task Implementation Guide

## Description
This rule provides a structured approach for handling @TODO comments and implementing the associated tasks. It ensures consistent documentation and implementation of TODO items across the codebase.

## Trigger Conditions
- Message contains "do TODO"
- When encountering [TODO](mdc:TODO) comments in code
- When assigned to implement a TODO task
- When creating new documentation for planned features

## Implementation Guidelines

### 1. Preparation Process
1. **Review Context**
   - take only the first TODO list item
   - Scan related files to understand the full context of the TODO task
   - Check if supporting files already address parts of the requirement. Leverage [DocumentationGuide.md](mdc:docs/DocumentationGuide.md) to find the relevant docs
   - Review relevant documentation in the appropriate folders 

2. **Documentation**
   - If updating existing functionality, update the relevant documentation
   - If creating new functionality, create appropriate documentation following the structure in `docs/DocumentationGuide.md`
   - Ensure all new documents are placed in the correct location within the documentation hierarchy

3. **Implementation**
   - Follow the architectural patterns defined in the project documentation
   - Apply consistent coding standards and patterns
   - Remove the @TODO comment when the task is completed
   - Add appropriate tests for new functionality

## Best Practices
- Always check existing files before creating new ones
- Keep documentation and implementation in sync
- Follow the project's established patterns and guidelines
- Update related documentation when implementing TODO items
- Add clear comments for any new TODO items you create

## Integration
- This rule works alongside other code and documentation rules
- It helps maintain consistency across the codebase
- It ensures proper documentation of implemented features

